OL,3,CLabour appears to haemorrhage seats as
OL,4,Cfirst local election results roll in
OL,6,FAlthough Labour's starting position
OL,7,Fmeans it retains control of Halton
OL,8,FCouncil, the shift in vote share
OL,9,Fcombined with losses elsewhere in the
OL,10,FNorth West point to a difficult night
OL,11,Ffor Sir Keir.
OL,13,FThose results included losses to
OL,14,FReform in Chorley, in Lancashire, and
OL,15,FWigan, in Greater Manchester.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/11
