OL,3,CLabour appears to haemorrhage seats as
OL,4,Cfirst local election results roll in
OL,6,FIn Hartlepool, Reform won all 12 seats
OL,7,Fon offer, pushing the previously
OL,8,FLabour-held council into no overall
OL,9,Fcontrol, while Labour also lost
OL,10,Fcontrol of Redditch, where Reform won
OL,11,Feight of the nine seats up for
OL,12,Felection.
OL,14,FIn the first three councils to
OL,15,Fcomplete their counts, Labour lost 26
OL,16,Fseats while Reform gained 34.
OL,18,FA national drubbing is likely to
OL,19,Freignite speculation about Sir Keir's
OL,20,Fleadership of the party and the
OL,21,Fcountry.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
