OL,3,CLabour appears to haemorrhage seats as
OL,4,Cfirst local election results roll in
OL,6,FBefore polls closed, The Times
OL,7,Freported that Energy Secretary and
OL,8,Fformer Labour leader Ed Miliband had
OL,9,Fprivately urged the Prime Minister to
OL,10,Fset out a timetable for his departure
OL,11,Fafter the elections.
OL,13,FBut Deputy Prime Minister David Lammy
OL,14,Furged his party not to play "pass the
OL,15,Fparcel" with the leadership in
OL,16,Fresponse to the election results.
OL,26,@vD@]OUwD@GO]
