OL,3,CLabour appears to haemorrhage seats as
OL,4,Cfirst local election results roll in
OL,6,FHe told the BBC there were "questions
OL,7,Fthat we have to answer" but there were
OL,8,F"no circumstances in which the answer
OL,9,Fto the questions that the British
OL,10,Fpeople are raising is to change the
OL,11,Fleader yet again".
OL,13,FLabour sources also pointed to the
OL,14,Fheavy defeat suffered by the party in
OL,15,F1999 before Sir Tony Blair went on to
OL,16,Fwin re-election by a landslide in 2001.
OL,26,@nD@\OUoD@WO]pD@AOUsD@QO]
