OL,3,CLabour appears to haemorrhage seats as
OL,4,Cfirst local election results roll in
OL,6,FMeanwhile, Nigel Farage's Reform UK is
OL,7,Fset to make significant gains,
OL,8,Fbuilding on last year's local
OL,9,Felections that saw the party pick up
OL,10,Falmost 700 councillors and take
OL,11,Fcontrol of 10 authorities.
OL,13,FPointing to the fragmentation of the
OL,14,Ftraditional two-party duopoly,
OL,15,FReform's Zia Yusuf told the Press
OL,16,FAssociation he expected to see "a
OL,17,Fturquoise wave" across Labour's
OL,18,Ftraditional heartlands.
OL,26,@xD@`OUyD@OO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
