OL,3,CLabour appears to haemorrhage seats as
OL,4,Cfirst local election results roll in
OL,6,FAlmost 25,000 candidates were fighting
OL,7,Fto be elected to more than 5,000 seats
OL,8,Fon 136 councils across England, where
OL,9,Fsix local mayoral contests also took
OL,10,Fplace.
OL,12,FIn Scotland, all 129 seats were up for
OL,13,Felection at Holyrood while voters in
OL,14,FWales were choosing 96 members of the
OL,15,FSenedd.
OL,17,FVotes in Wales and Scotland are not
OL,18,Fdue to be counted until later on
OL,19,FFriday, but both elections are
OL,20,Fexpected to pile further pressure on
OL,21,Fthe Prime Minister.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
